features: Straighten up your files and keep documents organized with these letter size 1/3-cut reinforced tab file folders (11-5/8" W x 9-1/2" H overall, 9" H body) designed for your filing needs
Everything has its place with this box of 100 manila folders with reinforced tabs designed for desktop and drawer filing, maintaining the order you need to keep your office organized
11 point manila paper stock protects important papers and makes it easy to find what you need at a glance, and reinforced two-ply tabs have extra strength and durability where you need it most
Organize your files with this classic solution, perfect for bills, recipes, projects, correspondence, vehicle records, client information and more
Proudly made in the USA, these manila file folders contain 10% recycled content, 10% post-consumer material and are SFI Sourcing Certified; Available in additional colors
body.description: Product Description Organize or update your paperwork filing, making it easy to find the documents you need when you need them. Smead’s File Folders are designed to keep your desktop or drawer filing system tidy. Documents are easy to find when properly filed in your office or home. Your office filing can achieve better organization with fewer lost and damaged documents when you incorporate a filing system in your office. Includes 100 letter size folders (11-5/8" W x 9-1/2" H overall, 9" H body) in manila with a 1/3-cut reinforced tab for printed or handwritten labels. Two-ply reinforced tabs provide extra strength where you need it most, making frequently accessed files tougher. Durable 11 point stock folders are scored for 3/4” expansion. Improve filing efficiency when you can find exactly what you need at your fingertips. Bring order to your household and office with our colorful filing solutions. Use for school handouts and projects. Proudly made in the USA, these file folders contain 10% recycled content, 10% post-consumer material and are SFI Sourcing Certified. From the Manufacturer Smead Reinforced 2-Ply File FoldersReinforced 2-ply tabs for extra durability and longer life.Rainbow of colors for organizing by project type or category.Perfect for everyday use.Multiple tab positions to fit any vertical or lateral filing system.Available in a variety of sizes and styles.Reinforced tabs provide extra strength where you need it most, so you get longer life and lower replacement costs. Available in a variety of colors to organize by project type or category. Multiple tab options to work with any filing system. Reinforced 2-Ply TabsThe reinforced double-thick tab adds extra strength and durability at the point of greatest wear. Great folder for everyday use. Lower Replacement CostsThe 2-ply reinforced tab will hold up to frequent use, so you won’t have to replace the folders as often. These quality file folders are extra durable and will save you money over time. Rainbow of Colors and SizesUse a rainbow of colors to organize by category or project type. reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on March 16, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Perfect - Just What I Needed!
reviews.reviewText: Every few years, I replace my old folders with new ones because the tabs are so flimsy, so after searching on AMAZON for folders with a sturdy tab - I found these! The reinforced tabs are great, so my folders should hold up for more than a few years now.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 31, 2022
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Happy with purchase
reviews.reviewText: Seemed sturdy enough, good value, easy transaction.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 30, 2018
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Letter sized "manilla folders" with three different tab layouts on top.
reviews.reviewText: Not much to say about letter sized folders... They exist. They seem to be of OK quality. And Amazon shipped them to me directly so I didn't have to haul my lazy self to the office supply store (yea).The three different tab layouts are "far left", "far right", and "center". I had a choice of this or one of the "all left or all right", and figured a variety would be easier to read when the folders are clustered together. The price seemed the best of the ones I was able to locate, so gave it a shot and am not disappointed. Then again, these are just file folders, so not much to go wrong with.
